    {
      "text": "Gradius Advance is a horizontally scrolling shooter video game developed by Mobile21 and published by Konami, originally released in Europe in November 2001. It was released in the United States as Gradius Galaxies later in the same month and in Japan as Gradius Generation in January 2002. It is the only Gradius title available for the Game Boy Advance. The game's plot is set between Gradius III and Gradius Gaiden. Bacterion was developing a powerful weapon to use against the planet Gradius, but it was destroyed. A few years later it crashed on a planet and the planet gradually changed into a mechanical fortress. The planet Gradius then sent the Vic Viper to stop it.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
